The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, June 4, 2007

 Science camp

 Mad Science Calcutta will host Academy of Future Space Explorers Summer Camp, developed at Nasa, at Science City, 10am to 12.30pm.

 Workshop

 Workshop on Water, Climatic Change and Sustainable Development, at National Institute of Technical Teachers Training and Research, 10.30am. To be followed by a curtain-raiser on World Environment Day, 3.30pm.

 Personality development workshop for children at Maheshwari Bhavan, off Sova Ram Bysack Street, 11am to 6pm.

 Kids stage

 National Childrens Theatre Fest, in association with Paschimbanga Natya Akademi, at Rabindra Sadan. Today: Maanush, 4pm, Hum Kunware Rahe, 5pm, Swapno Dekha, 6pm, Gandhigiri, 7pm, and Tota Kahini, 8pm.

 Lenswork

 Annual Photography Exhibition 2007 at Kumar Ashutosh Institution, 5pm to 9pm.

 The Times: Then and Now (Samay Takhan, Samay Ekhan), an exhibition of photographs on Tebhaga and Nandigram, at Boi-Chitra, College Street Coffee House, 3pm to 8pm.

 Eye on art

 Summer Show, an exhibition of works by various artists from across India, at CIMA Gallery, 3pm to 7pm.

 A Handful of Dignity, a digital vectored art exhibition by Debarshi Roy, at Oxford Bookstore, 10.30am to 7pm.




